# Flask MongoDB CRUD App  

A full-stack web app built with **Python (Flask)** and **MongoDB Atlas** that submits user data to a database and displays success/error messages.  

## Features  
âœ… User form submission  
âœ… MongoDB Atlas integration  
âœ… Error handling & redirects  
âœ… Responsive frontend  

## Tech Stack  
- **Backend**: Python, Flask  
- **Database**: MongoDB Atlas  
- **Frontend**: HTML/CSS  

## Setup  
1. Clone repo:  
   ```bash
   git clone https://github.com/sherkhanp1/Tutedude_Devops/new/main
Install dependencies:

bash
pip install -r requirements.txt
Add your .env file (use .env.example as a template).

Run:

bash
python app.py
